{"name":"Spell Scroll: Create Food and Water","type":"consumable","img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-create-food-and-water.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>A spell scroll bears the words of a single spell, written in a mystical cipher. If the spell is on your class's spell list, you can use an action to read the scroll and cast its spell without having to provide any of the spell's components. Otherwise, the scroll is unintelligible.</p><hr /><h3>Create Food and Water (Level 3)</h3><hr /><div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>You create 45 pounds of food and 30 gallons of water on the ground or in containers within range, enough to sustain up to fifteen humanoids or five steeds for 24 hours. The food is bland but nourishing, and spoils if uneaten after 24 hours. The water is clean and doesn't go bad.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><hr /><h3>Scroll Details</h3><hr />\n<p>If the spell is on your class's spell list but of a higher level than you can normally cast, you must make an ability check using your spellcasting ability to determine whether you cast it successfully. The DC is 13. On a failed check, the spell disappears from the scroll with no other effect.</p>\n<p>Once the spell is cast, the words on the scroll fade, and the scroll itself crumbles to dust.</p>\n<p>The level of the spell on the scroll determines the spell's saving throw DC and attack bonus, as well as the scroll's rarity.</p>\n<p><strong>Save DC</strong>: 15<br /><strong>Attack bonus</strong>: +7.</p>\n<p>A wizard spell on a spell scroll can be copied just as spells in spellbooks can be copied. When a spell is copied from a spell scroll, the copier must succeed on an Intelligence (Arcana) check with a DC equal to 13. If the check succeeds, the spell is successfully copied. Whether the check succeeds or fails, the spell scroll is destroyed.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":200,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"